<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1869-10-05T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1869-10-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="485" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d485">
                            <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Boutwell</persName>,
                                    Secretary of the Treasury, to Mr. <persName type="to">Rumley</persName>, collector</hi>.</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <dateline><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Treasury
                                        Department</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1869-10-05"><hi rend="italic">October</hi> 5,
                                1869</date>.</dateline>
                            <p rend="flushleft"><hi rend="smallcaps">D. Rumley</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Collector of Customs, Wilmington, North
                                    Carolina:</hi></p>
                            <p>Your course in the case of the Hornet is approved. Who is retained as
                                counsel? You will hold the Hornet, under the eleventh section of the
                                act of 1818, until directed by the President to release her.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>GEO. S. BOUTWELL,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Secretary,
                                        &amp;c.</hi></signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>